Description: Coil-woven basket and cover with inwoven decoration and a leather centre.
Curator's comments: Nos.1 to 3 are recorded as "Baskets made by women for small articles; the larger kind to hold olive oil." See Margaret M. Vale, ‘Siwa: Jewelry, costume, and life in an Egyptian Oasis’, 2015
Acquisition notes: Af1920,1206.1 to 16 were given by W Seymour Walker; they are all objects that he had collected in the Siwa Oasis in Egypt, and the register contains information that he had recorded about the objects..
